    "title": "Three new asporogenous yeasts found in industrial waste water.",
    "abstract": "Representatives of three new asporogenous species, Candida flavificans, Candida inositophila, and Torulopsis sorbophila were isolated from washings of ion-exchange resin in a guanosine monophosphate manufacturing plant. The DNA base composition, proton-magnetic-resonance spectrum of extracted polysaccharides, and serological characteristics of the yeasts were investigated in addition to the characteristics commonly employed. Descriptions of the new species are given.",
